item.title: Does sitting cause big thighs?
item.description: Weight Gain Moving causes your muscles to release molecules like lipoprotein lipase, which helps process the fats and sugars you eat. item.title: Why do they put caffeine in painkillers?
item.description: Caffeine is added to some painkillers, such as paracetamol and ibuprofen, to help them work better. A recent Cochrane review of evidence found that added caffeine had a small but significant effect, amounting to an additional 5-10% of patients achieving a good level of pain relief. Why is caffeine in some pain relievers? Caffeine could reduce pain sensation through its effects on adenosine receptors (14-18). Caffeine seems to express its direct effect via central blocking of adenosine receptors that influence pain signaling or by blocking of peripheral adenosine receptors on sensory afferents.

item.title: What does it mean when peroxide bubbles?
item.description: When poured onto a cut or scrape, hydrogen peroxide encounters blood and damaged skin cells. item.title: When did IIII become IV?
item.description: In the middle ages in Europe, IIII was generally used, not IV, to express the Roman numeral 4 until around the 17th century. In fact, you can see the notation IIII on mechanical turret clocks that were made before around the 17th century. Why did IIII change to IV? When Roman numerals were in use by the Roman Empire, the name of the Romans' supreme deity, Jupiter, was spelled as IVPPITER in Latin.

item.title: Why is my freezer blowing warm air?
item.description: Answer If the condenser coils are dusty or have not been cleaned in a long time, they should be thoroughly cleaned. The evaporator fan motor is responsible for drawing air over the evaporator coils and circulating it throughout the refrigerator. The freezer will not cool if the evaporator fan motor is not functioning properly. It is impossible for the freezer to chill if the compressor is not operating.
